@@TJvBitBtn.HotGlyph
Summary
  Specifies the bitmap that appears on the button when the mouse points to it.
Description
  Set HotGlyph to a bitmap object that contains the image that should appear on the face of the
  button when the mouse passes over it at runtime. If HotGlyph is unassigned, the button retains its
  regular image (specified by the Glyph property) when the mouse passes over the button.
See Also
  TJvBitBtn.HotTrack, TJvBitBtn.HotTrackFont

